              },
              "free_text": [
                " 14UD tandem accelerator at the",
                "Australian National University"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Enriched (>99%) 208PbS targets, of  thickness approx.",
                "84 mu-g/cm2, evaporated onto a 15 microg/cm2 C backing.",
                "For the ER measurements, a target backed by an Al",
                "catcher foil was used; the Al foil was 550 mu-g/cm2",
                "in thickness, so as to stop the recoiling heavy",
                "residues well within the foil.  The reaction products",
                "were identified by their distinctive alfa-energies",
                "and half-lives (182 ns to  23.9 min)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC",
                "PS",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For normalization, two monitor",
                "detectors, placed at angles of 22.5 degrees above",
                "and below the beam axis, measured the elastically",
                "scattered beam particles. Fission fragments",
                "following fusion were detected in the CUBE detector",
                "array, using a large area (357 mm x 284 mm) position",
                "sensitive multiwire proportional counter covering",
                "laboratory angles from 95-170 degrees. However, the",
                "measurements were restricted to the angular range",
                "95-165 degrees, since an annular silicon surface",
                "barrier detector was placed 8 cm from the target, at",
                "a mean angle of 174 degrees, to detect the decay",
                "alfa-particles from the evaporation residues."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
